ğŸƒ Runner-Up Score â€“ Python
ğŸ“Œ Problem Statement

Given the participants' score sheet for your University Sports Day, you are required to find the runner-up score.

You are given n scores. Store them in a list and find the score of the runner-up.

ğŸ§¾ Input Format

The first line contains an integer n (number of participants).

The second line contains an array A of n integers separated by spaces.

ğŸ“¤ Output Format

Print the runner-up score (second highest distinct score).

ğŸ§ª Sample Input
5
2 3 6 6 5

âœ… Sample Output
5

ğŸ§  Explanation

Given the list [2, 3, 6, 6, 5]:

The maximum score is 6

The second maximum (runner-up) score is 5

Hence, the output is 5.

ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ’» Python Solution


if __name__ == '__main__':
    n = int(input())
    arr = map(int, input().split())
    
    unique_scores = list(set(arr))
    unique_scores.sort(reverse=True)
    
    Runner_Up = unique_scores[1]
    print(Runner_Up)
